er}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/17457206?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/sgaoae","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3NDU3MjA2","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"sgaoae","type":"User","id":17457206,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"NONE","body":"I write a new example using three box geometry and MeshBasicMaterial https:\/\/jsfiddle.net\/errd49Lk\/1\/\r\n\r\nI have found such pattern:\r\n1. the order depends on the creation order\r\na: transparent: false, depthTest: false\r\nb: transparent: false, depthTest: false\r\n\r\n2. the order depends on the creation order\r\na: transparent: false, depthTest: false\r\nb: transparent: false, depthTest: true\r\n\r\n3. the order depends on the position\r\na: transparent: false, depthTest: true\r\nb: transparent: false, depthTest: true\r\n\r\nI am very curious about pattern 2. So the problem could be related to depthTest. \r\n\r\nI hope it helps. \r\n@mrdoob ","created_at":"2017-11-24T12:26:16.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12737#issuecomment-346817772","id":346817772,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12737","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NjgxNzc3Mg==","updated_at":"2017-11-24T12:28:08.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/346817772","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/17457206?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/sgaoae","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3NDU3MjA2","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"sgaoae","type":"User","id":17457206,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"NONE","body":"I think I have found the reason for the jsfiddle example. \r\nThe reason should be that disabling depthTest also disables depthWrite in webgl. \r\n\r\nFor https:\/\/jsfiddle.net\/v2udjzbe\/: \r\nFront box: yellow, depthTest: false, transparent: false\r\nBack box: red, depthTest: true, transparent: false\r\n\r\nFront box is drawn first. its color is drawn on the screen and the depth buffer is not updated. \r\nBack box is drawn after that, as the depth of front box is not written in depth buffer, its color will be drawn and override the front box color. \r\n\r\nFor https:\/\/jsfiddle.net\/errd49Lk\/1\/: \r\ncube0: blue, depthTest: false, 1st closest to camera\r\ncube1: green, depthTest: true, 2nd closest to camera\r\ncube2: red, depthTest: true, 3rd closest to camera\r\n\r\ncube0 is drawn first. its color is drawn on the screen and the depth buffer is not updated. \r\ncube1 is drawn after that, as the depth of cube0 is not written in depth buffer, its color will be drawn and override the cube0 color. \r\ncube2 is drawn after that, as the depth of cube0 is not written in depth buffer, its color will be drawn and override the cube0 color, but as the depth of cube1 is written, its color will not override cube1 color. \r\n\r\nSo by setting depthTest=false, we automatically set depthWrite=false in rendering although the depthWrite value in Material is not updated. Am I right?\r\nBut I want the cube0 and front box to appear before certain other objects, is there a way to achieve such effects without setting renderOrder? I have lots of objects in my scene and I just don't want to specify for each of them. \r\nOr is there a way to turn on depthWrite whiling setting depthTest to false?\r\n\r\nThank you very much. @mrdoob ","created_at":"2017-11-24T13:37:02.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12737#issuecomment-346830339","id":346830339,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12737","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NjgzMDMzOQ==","updated_at":"2017-11-24T13:37:02.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/346830339","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/17457206?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/sgaoae","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3NDU3MjA2","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"sgaoae","type":"User","id":17457206,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/sgaoae\/follow